020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.DEPRECATED;
023import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.INTERNAL;
024import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
025import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
026
027import javax.lang.model.element.TypeParameterElement;
028import javax.lang.model.type.ArrayType;
029import java.io.UncheckedIOException;
030import java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType;
031import java.lang.reflect.Type;
032import java.util.ArrayList;
033import java.util.List;
034import java.util.Map;
035
036import org.apiguardian.api.API;
037import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
038import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.AnnotationSpec;
039import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.ArrayTypeName;
040import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.TypeName;
041import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.TypeVariableName;
042
043/**
044 *  The implementation of
045 *  {@link TypeNameImpl}
046 *  for array types.
047 *
048 *  @author Square,Inc.
049 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
050 *  @version $Id: ArrayTypeNameImpl.java 1062 2023-09-25 23:11:41Z tquadrat $
051 *  @since 0.0.5
052 *
053 *  @UMLGraph.link
054 */
055@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: ArrayTypeNameImpl.java 1062 2023-09-25 23:11:41Z tquadrat $" )
056@API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.5" )
057public final class ArrayTypeNameImpl extends TypeNameImpl implements ArrayTypeName
058{
059        /*------------*\
060    ====** Attributes **=======================================================
061        \*------------*/
062    /**
063     *  The array component type.
064     */
065    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
066    private final TypeNameImpl m_ComponentType;
067
068        /*--------------*\
069    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
070        \*--------------*/
071    /**
072     *  Creates a new {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} instance.
073     *
074     *  @param  componentType   The type of the array components.
075     */
076    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
077    public ArrayTypeNameImpl( final TypeNameImpl componentType ) { this( componentType, new ArrayList<>() ); }
078
079    /**
080     *  Creates a new {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} instance.
081     *
082     *  @param  componentType   The type of the array components.
083     *  @param  annotations The annotations for this array type name.
084     */
085    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
086    public ArrayTypeNameImpl( final TypeNameImpl componentType, final List<AnnotationSpecImpl> annotations )
087    {
088        super( annotations );
089        m_ComponentType = requireNonNullArgument( componentType, "componentType" );
090    }   //  ArrayTypeNameImpl()
091
092        /*---------*\
093    ====** Methods **==========================================================
094        \*---------*/
095    /**
096     *  {@inheritDoc}
097     */
098    @Override
099    public final ArrayTypeNameImpl annotated( final List<AnnotationSpec> annotations )
100    {
101        return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( getComponentType(), concatAnnotations( annotations ) );
102    }   //  annotated()
103
104    /**
105     *  {@inheritDoc}
106     */
107    @Override
108    public final TypeName componentType() { return getComponentType(); }
109
110    /**
111     *  {@inheritDoc}
112     */
113    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
114    @Override
115    public final CodeWriter emit( final CodeWriter out ) throws UncheckedIOException { return emit( out, false ); }
116
117    /**
118     *  Emits this type name instance to the given
119     *  {@link CodeWriter}.
120     *
121     *  @param  out The code writer.
122     *  @param  varargs {@code true} if the array should be emitted as varargs
123     *      (obviously this affects only arrays used in method signatures),
124     *      {@code false} for the usual representation.
125     *  @return The code writer.
126     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
127     *      output target.
128     */
129    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
130    public final CodeWriter emit( final CodeWriter out, final boolean varargs ) throws UncheckedIOException
131    {
132        final var retValue = requireNonNullArgument( out, "out" );
133        emitLeafType( retValue );
134        emitBrackets( retValue, varargs );
135
136        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
137        return retValue;
138    }   //  emit()
139
140    /**
141     *  Emits the annotations and the brackets for the array.
142     *
143     *  @param  out The code writer.
144     *  @param  varargs {@code true} if the array should be emitted as varargs
145     *      (obviously this affects only arrays used in method signatures),
146     *      {@code false} for the usual representation.
147     *  @return The code writer.
148     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
149     *      output target.
150     */
151    @SuppressWarnings( {"UnusedReturnValue", "UseOfConcreteClass"} )
152    private final CodeWriter emitBrackets( final CodeWriter out, final boolean varargs ) throws UncheckedIOException
153    {
154        final var retValue = requireNonNullArgument( out, "out" );
155        if( isAnnotated() )
156        {
157            retValue.emit( " " );
158            emitAnnotations( retValue );
159        }
160
161        final var arrayInArray = asArray( getComponentType() );
162        if( arrayInArray.isPresent() )
163        {
164            retValue.emit( "[]" );
165            arrayInArray.get().emitBrackets( retValue, varargs );
166        }
167        else
168        {
169            //---* Last bracket *----------------------------------------------
170            retValue.emit( varargs ? "..." : "[]" );
171        }
172
173        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
174        return retValue;
175    }   //  emitBrackets()
176
177    /**
178     *  Emits the array's component type.
179     *
180     *  @param  out The code writer.
181     *  @return The code writer.
182     *  @throws UncheckedIOException Something went wrong when writing to the
183     *      output target.
184     */
185    @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
186    private final CodeWriter emitLeafType( final CodeWriter out ) throws UncheckedIOException
187    {
188        final var arrayInArray = asArray( getComponentType() );
189        final var retValue = arrayInArray.isPresent()
190            ? arrayInArray.get().emitLeafType( out )
191            : getComponentType().emit( out );
192
193        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
194        return retValue;
195    }   //  emitLeafType()
196
197    /**
198     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type
199     *  that is equivalent to {@code mirror}.
200     *
201     *  @param  mirror  The mirror for the array.
202     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
203     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
204     */
205    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
206    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl from( final ArrayType mirror, final Map<TypeParameterElement,TypeVariableNameImpl> typeVariables )
207    {
208        final var retValue = new ArrayTypeNameImpl( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( mirror, "mirror" ).getComponentType(), typeVariables ) );
209
210        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
211        return retValue;
212    }   //  from()
213
214    /**
215     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type that
216     *  is equivalent to {@code type}.
217     *
218     *  @param  type    The array type.
219     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
220     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
221     */
222    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
223    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl from( final GenericArrayType type, final Map<Type,TypeVariableName> typeVariables )
224    {
225        final var retValue = of( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( type, "type" ).getGenericComponentType(), typeVariables ) );
226
227        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
228        return retValue;
229    }   //  from()
230
231    /**
232     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type
233     *  that is equivalent to {@code mirror}.
234     *
235     *  @param  mirror  The mirror for the array.
236     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
237     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
238     *
239     *  @deprecated Use
240     *      {@link #from(ArrayType,Map)}
241     *      instead.
242     */
243    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
244    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
245    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl get( final ArrayType mirror, final Map<TypeParameterElement,TypeVariableNameImpl> typeVariables )
246    {
247        final var retValue = from( mirror, typeVariables);
248
249        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
250        return retValue;
251    }   //  get()
252
253    /**
254     *  Returns an instance of {@code ArrayTypeNameImpl} for an array type that
255     *  is equivalent to {@code type}.
256     *
257     *  @param  type    The array type.
258     *  @param  typeVariables   The type variables.
259     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
260     *
261     *  @deprecated Use
262     *      {@link #from(GenericArrayType,Map)}
263     *      instead.
264     */
265    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
266    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
267    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl get( final GenericArrayType type, final Map<Type,TypeVariableName> typeVariables )
268    {
269        final var retValue = from( type, typeVariables );
270
271        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
272        return retValue;
273    }   //  get()
274
275    /**
276     *  Returns the array component type.
277     *
278     * @return The array component type.
279     */
280    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface"} )
281    public final TypeNameImpl getComponentType() { return m_ComponentType; }
282
283    /**
284     *  Returns an array type whose elements are all instances of the given
285     *  component type.
286     *
287     *  @param  componentType   The component type.
288     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
289     */
290    public static ArrayTypeNameImpl of( final Type componentType )
291    {
292        return of( TypeNameImpl.from( requireNonNullArgument( componentType, "componentType" ) ) );
293    }   //  of()
294
295    /**
296     *  Returns an array type whose elements are all instances of the given
297     *  component type.
298     *
299     *  @param  componentType   The component type.
300     *  @return The new instance of {@code ArrayTypeName}.
301     */
302    public static final ArrayTypeNameImpl of( final TypeName componentType )
303    {
304        return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( (TypeNameImpl) componentType );
305    }   //  of()
306
307    /**
308     *  {@inheritDoc}
309     */
310    @Override
311    public final ArrayTypeNameImpl withoutAnnotations() { return new ArrayTypeNameImpl( getComponentType() ); }
312}
313//  class ArrayTypeNameImpl
